ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Conflict Policy: Conclusion', 'conflict-policy-conclusion', '<h2>Conflict Policy: Conclusion</h2>
<blockquote><p><em>If individual team members are unable to resolve a conflict on their own, it is their responsibility to report the conflict to their supervisor for resolution assistance.</em></p></blockquote>
<p>Management-lead conflict resolution will utilize the approaches and strategies outlined in this guide. If management-lead mediation is unable to resolve the conflict, management may seek mediation via a third-party mediator.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>Innovative Air Technologies is dedicated to cultivating a workplace where employees can thrive in a positive and respectful atmosphere.</strong></p></blockquote>
<p>This conflict resolution policy serves as a guide to proactively address conflicts, promote open communication, and uphold the well-being of our employees, contributing to the overall success of our organization.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong><em>Together</em>, we strive to maintain a workplace characterized by collaboration, innovation, and mutual respect.</strong></p></blockquote>', 53, TRUE, 2
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Understanding Our Discipline Policy', 'discipline-policy-overview', '<h2>Understanding Our Discipline Policy</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Understanding Discipline Policy in Our Company video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>At Innovative Air Technologies, our mission is to foster a workplace built on respect, integrity, and collaboration. Our Discipline Policy serves as a framework to ensure consistency, fairness, and accountability in addressing behavior or performance issues that do not align with our core values or expectations.</p>
<p>This policy is designed not just to enforce standards but to provide employees with clear opportunities to learn, improve and succeed. By working together to address challenges constructively, we aim to maintain a positive, productive environment where everyone can thrive.</p>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: "Behave yourself" meme — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>', 54, TRUE, 3
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Grounds for Disciplinary Action', 'discipline-grounds-for-action', '<h2>Grounds for Disciplinary Action</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Grounds for Disciplinary Action Review video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>At Innovative Air Technologies, we''ve got a clear guide that lays out what could get you in hot water, discipline-wise. It''s like a roadmap showing you the do''s and don''ts to help you steer clear of trouble. This list is not comprehensive; rather, it is examples of the types of conduct that this company does not tolerate.</p>
<h3>Examples of behavior that may lead to disciplinary measures:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Engaging in acts of discrimination or harassment in the workplace.</li>
<li>Possessing, distributing or being under the influence of illicit controlled substances.</li>
<li>Being under the influence of a controlled substance or alcohol at work, on company premises, or while engaged in company business.</li>
<li>Unauthorized use of company property, equipment, devices, or assets.</li>
<li>Damage, destruction or theft of company property, equipment, devices, or assets.</li>
<li>Removing company property without prior authorization or disseminating company information without authorization.</li>
<li>Falsification, misrepresentation or omission of company information, documents, or records.</li>
<li>Lying, associated to issues pertaining to company business and policies</li>
<li>Insubordination or refusal to comply with directives.</li>
<li>Failing to adequately perform job responsibilities.</li>
<li>Excessive or unexcused absenteeism or tardiness.</li>
<li>Disclosing confidential or proprietary company information without permission.</li>
<li>Illegal or violent activity, on company property or during company business</li>
<li>Falsifying injury reports or reasons for leave.</li>
<li>Possessing unauthorized weapons on premises.</li>
<li>Disregard for safety and security procedures.</li>
<li>Disparaging or disrespecting supervisors and/or co-workers.</li>
<li>Gossip.</li>
<li>Any other action or conduct that is inconsistent with company policies, procedures, values, or expectations.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Just a heads-up,</strong> the list isn''t the be-all and end-all. It doesn''t cover every single thing that could land you in hot water. We get that every situation is its own beast, so we promise to look at things on a case-by-case basis, weighing up what happened and how serious it is before deciding on any disciplinary action.</p>', 55, TRUE, 4
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Disciplinary Procedures', 'discipline-procedures', '<h2>Disciplinary Procedures</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Disciplinary Procedures video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>The below steps are typically taken to handle all disciplinary actions of the company. Evaluation of each infraction by the manager or supervisor determines the steps taken.</p>
<ol>
<li>Step 1: Verbal Warning/Counseling</li>
<li>Step 2: Written Warning</li>
<li>Step 3: Employee Suspension</li>
<li>Step 4: Termination</li>
</ol>
<h3>Step 1: Verbal Warning/Counseling</h3>
<p>Manager will have a conversation with the employee regarding the facts of the infraction, the seriousness of the incident and finally the company''s expectation that the employee will not repeat said infraction in the future. This conversation is intended to help the employee understand how their behaviors need to change. The infraction will be documented in the employee''s file and be subject to review during performance evaluations.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Written Warning</h3>
<p>Manager will have a follow-up conversation along with a formal, written warning. The written warning will include a description of the infraction, along with the manager''s expectation of the employee''s behavior, description of the consequences if the expectations are not met, and a time frame for meeting expectations. The formal written warning will be signed by the employee and manager that the conversation took place; this not meant as an admission of guilt. A copy will be given to the employee for his/her record.</p>
<h3>Step 3: Employee Suspension and Improvement Plan</h3>
<p>Manager to document infraction and discuss with employee. The employee is then escorted to leave the premise and not return until suspension has ended. Upon return an action plan will be put in place to correct the behavior and prevent recurrences. Failure to follow will result in immediate termination.</p>
<h3>Step 4: Termination</h3>
<p>Manager to document infraction and discuss with employee. The employee is then escorted to gather personal items prior to leaving the premises — any unruly behavior forfeits this. Upon termination, an employee is required to:</p>
<ol>
<li>Turn in all reports and paperwork required to be completed by the employee when due and no later than the last day of work.</li>
<li>Return all files, documents, equipment, keys, access cards, software or other property belonging to the company that are in the employee''s possession, custody or control, and turn in all passwords to his/her supervisor.</li>
</ol>', 56, TRUE, 4
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Discipline Policy Enforcement', 'discipline-policy-enforcement', '<h2>Discipline Policy Enforcement</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Understanding Discipline Policy Enforcement video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>A 30-day virtual clock will start with each different infraction. If a repeat infraction of the same rule is committed in that time period the following steps will be taken and the clock will restart with each infraction. After 30 days with no infractions, the clock expires.</p>
<p>With each additional infraction the level of discipline increases up to and including termination.</p>
<p>All infractions are logged in the employee''s file.</p>
<ul>
<li>Minor infractions (ex: tardy, disregard for safety) will start 30-day virtual clock.</li>
<li>Major infractions (ex: theft, drugs, destruction, lying, insubordination) will be immediately assessed by manager.</li>
</ul>', 57, TRUE, 3
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
