<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Understanding the Discipline Form video tutorial — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p><a href="https://www.dehumidifiers.com/discipline-form">Discipline Form | Dehumidifiers.com</a></p>', 58, TRUE, 2
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Voluntary Termination: Overview', 'voluntary-termination-overview', '<h2>Voluntary Termination: Overview</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Understanding Voluntary Termination video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>The company recognizes that personal situations may arise which require a voluntary termination of employment. Should this occur, the company requests that the employee provide two weeks advance notice in writing. This request does not alter an employee''s at-will relationship with the company. All rights and privileges of employment with the company terminate upon the date of separation. As further discussed in our Work Performance Policy, terminating employees are required to return all company property assigned to them. Failure to do so may result in the withholding of their final paycheck.</p>
<h3>Upon voluntary termination, an employee is required to:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Continue to work until the last scheduled day of employment.</li>
<li>Turn in all reports and paperwork required to be completed by the employee when due and no later than the last day of work.</li>
<li>Return all files, documents, equipment, keys, access cards, software, or other property belonging to the company that are in the employee''s possession, custody, or control, and turn in all passwords to his/her supervisor.</li>
<li>Participate in an exit interview as requested by supervisor.</li>
</ol>', 59, TRUE, 3
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Final Paycheck', 'voluntary-termination-final-paycheck', '<h2>Final Paycheck</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Final Paycheck Information video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>If you decide to part ways with the company, don''t sweat it about your last paycheck. You''ll get it during the next pay cycle. And if you can''t swing by to pick it up or have it directly deposited for some reason, we''ll just mail it over to the address we have for you.</p>
<p>And just a heads up — if you''ve dipped into more PTO than you had, we''ll need to subtract those negative hours from your final paycheck.</p>', 60, TRUE, 2
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
